4 HR____ COMMENDING MR. ARTHUR J. SCOTT ON THE OCCASION OF HIS
5 RETIREMENT.
6
7 WHEREAS, with great pride and special pleasure,
8 highest commendations are conveyed to Mr. Arthur J. Scott on
9 the occasion of his retirement after 40 years of service to
10 Jackson Middle School in Clarke County; and
11 WHEREAS, Mr. Scott began his career at Jackson Middle
12 School on June 22, 1986, as the school's custodian under the
13 administration of Dr. Ronald M. Powe; and
14 WHEREAS, Mr. Scott has been a dedicated caretaker of
15 the building and the people in it, often encouraging
16 coworkers who were experiencing troubles; his work ethic is
17 beyond reproach because he believes the work you do reflects
18 who you are in your heart; he has also been determined to be
19 a role model to young men on how to set a good moral
20 standard for themselves, no matter where they are in their
21 life's journey; and
22 WHEREAS, Mr. Scott joined the Educational Support
23 Personnel Organization, where he served as the building
24 representative and, later, the president for the local
25 chapter for eight terms; he was instrumental in acquiring a
26 sick leave bank for support personnel in the Clarke County
27 School System; and
28 WHEREAS, a strong believer in Christ, he gives all
Page 1

WHEREAS, a strong believer in Christ, he gives all
HR333 INTRODUCED
29 the glory to God for his long and successful service in
30 education; now therefore,
31 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
32 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That Arthur J. Scott is highly
33 commended on a job well done upon the close of his 40-year
34 career with Jackson Middle School, and this resolution is
35 offered to him in highest regard for his achievements and
36 hard work with best wishes for good health, joy, and
37 blessings in his well-earned retirement.
